This is a maven project incorporating java code which can be used to create a CDOClient and store models or run queries over the contents of a CDOStore/Server. To exploit this code, you just need to import the contents of this directory in the Application Development Environment of your choice and then:
(a) run "maven clean install" to compile the code and produce the respective jar file (b) run "maven exec:java" to run the code/client. The code is accompanied with a .properties file (eu.paasage.wp4.client.properties) through which it can be specified:
(a) the IP of the host on which the CDO Server runs.
(b) the port on which the CDO Server listens.

FUNCTIONALITY: This CDO client exposes the following functionality: 
(i) register the EPackage that map to the domain code to be manipulated
(ii) store a model into a CDOResource with a particular name
(iii) run a particular query according to a specific dialect (OCL, SQL, HQL) over the contents of the CDO Server / Store 
(iv) open a view, get its contents (and probably process them - depends on the user's purposes) and finally close the view.
Note: first functionality (EPackage registering) should be initially invoked in order to exploit the rest. The CDO session
created by instantiating the CDOClient should be closed in the end by calling the respective java method.

